FBIS4-8062 "dreeu069_i_94014" FBIS-EEU-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported Serb Tanks Roll Into Town AU1004164894 Paris AFP in English 1648 GMT 10 Apr 94 AU1004164894 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Sarajevo, April 10 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serb forces took control Sunday of the riverbank where the Moslem town of Gorazde is located, and Serb tanks rolled into the southern part of town, the United Nations said. UN spokesman Dacre Halloway said the Serb forces took over the bank after crossing the Drina river, which had been the frontline between the two warring parties. He said there was sniper fire outside the office of the UN High Commissioner for Refugees. Serb forces have been attacking the Gorazde enclave for the past two weeks.
